    {
      "id": "intro-orte",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Places in the city",
      "body": "# In the city\n\nThis lesson teaches you the most important places in a city and the words for giving directions.\n\nFor each noun, learn the **article** along with it (el or la) - it decides later whether a contraction happens.\n\n| Spanish | meaning |\n|---|---|\n| la calle | the street |\n| el banco | the bank |\n| la plaza | the square |\n| el museo | the museum |\n| la tienda | the shop |\n| la estación | the station |\n| el hotel | the hotel |\n| el restaurante | the restaurant |\n\n**The station** is *la estación* - with an accent on the ó."
    },
    {
      "id": "intro-praepositionen",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Prepositions of place",
      "body": "## Where is something?\n\nUse these prepositions to describe where a place is:\n\n- **en** - in / on: *Estoy en el hotel.* (I am in the hotel.)\n- **al lado de** - next to: *al lado del banco* (next to the bank)\n- **entre** - between: *entre la plaza y el museo* (between the square and the museum)\n- **enfrente de** - opposite: *enfrente de la estación* (opposite the station)\n\n## Directions\n\nFor directions you need:\n\n- **a la izquierda** - to the left\n- **a la derecha** - to the right\n- **todo recto** - straight ahead\n\nExample: *El museo está a la derecha.* (The museum is on the right.)"
    },
    {
      "id": "intro-verschmelzungen",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "The contractions: al and del",
      "body": "## The key rule: al and del\n\nIn Spanish, two short words contract with the article **el** into a single word. This is mandatory - the separated form is wrong.\n\n**a + el = al**\n\n- WRONG: ~~Voy a el banco.~~\n- RIGHT: **Voy al banco.** (I go to the bank.)\n\n**de + el = del**\n\n- WRONG: ~~al lado de el museo~~\n- RIGHT: **al lado del museo** (next to the museum)\n\n### Only with el!\n\nThe contraction happens **only** with the masculine singular article **el**. Nothing contracts with *la*, *los* or *las*:\n\n| Original | Contraction |\n|---|---|\n| a + el banco | **al** banco |\n| a + la tienda | a **la** tienda (no contraction) |\n| de + el museo | **del** museo |\n| de + la plaza | de **la** plaza (no contraction) |\n\nRemember: *Voy a la plaza* stays separate, but *Voy al banco* contracts."
    },
